column5: my old 8hp John Deere can take on bigger drifts than that thing
.........and gets two feet of driveway per gallon!

Front snow hood is too small. Air intake will plug up with snow and stall.  Now this is a snow blower. They just never stop. Easy to maintain and reliable. The other T.T.C. kept a fleet of these multi use machines for over 30 years   http://www.fairpoint.net/~jpierce/images/16TractorWithSnowblower.jpg
